<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jean de Florette (Bravo Sunday at 5 p.m., again at 10:30 p.m.): Part 1 of 
Claude Berri's superb adaptation of the Marcel Pagnol novel about greed and 
innocence. Towering performances from Yves Montand, Gerard Depardieu and Daniel 
Anteuil. (2:30) 
</P>
<P>
The Picture of Dorian Gray (Channel 5 Monday at 3:30 a.m.): Albert Lewin's 
memorably elegant version of the Oscar Wilde novel starring Hurd Hatfield and 
Angela Lansbury. 
</P>
<P>
White Zombie (Channel 7 Friday at 3 a.m.): Creepy vintage horror film with Bela 
Lugosi playing "Liebestraum" to robot-like Madge Bellamy. (1:30) 
</P>
<P>
Double Indemnity (Channel 5 Saturday at 1:30 a.m.): Billy Wilder and Raymond 
Chandler's gratifying film noir adapted from James M. Cain's steamy tale of 
no-good blond Barbara Stanwyck wreaking havoc on Fred MacMurray and Edward G. 
Robinson. (2:15) 
</P>
<P>
Little Big Man (Channel 11 Saturday at midnight): Arthur Penn's funny and 
imaginative 1970 revisionist Western, which shows what our love of tall tales 
of the Old West reveals about ourselves. With Dustin Hoffman, Faye Dunaway. 
(3:00) 
</P>
</TEXT>
