<TEXT>
<P>
I'd like to thank KTTV for its nearly complete presentation of "The Pirates of 
Penzance." It certainly was enjoyable, and I hardly missed that 15-20 minute 
block of story (including three songs) that the station chopped out of the film 
in one piece to make room for commercials! Gee, I sure hope KTTV can maintain 
its high standards in coming presentations of "The Two Musketeers," "The Three 
Horsemen of the Apocalypse" and, of course, that old favorite, "Ali Baba and 
the 31 (and 1/2) Thieves." Way to go, guys! 
</P>
<P>
Mark Jones, Sun Valley 
</P>
