<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALK LIKE A MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Littwin gives women a bad name. She praises women for being self-conscious, 
self-effacing and for taking up as little space as possible. These qualities 
are not feminine; they are neurotic. 
</P>
<P>
She says she wants equality. She wants revenge. She went into that room 
spoiling for a fight, carrying a lifetime of anger. Then she did the equivalent 
of driving into a parked car, and blamed it on the car. 
</P>
<P>
Littwin claims she speaks for all women when she says women have spent most of 
their lives trying to be one of the boys, and that she wants men to behave like 
girls. A real man doesn't behave like a girl. Neither does a real woman. 
</P>
<P>
LINDA CIVITELLO 
</P>
<P>
Culver City 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
