</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
. . . The animated "The Rescuers Down Under" -- about the Aussie adventures of 
those valiant mice, Miss Bianca, Bernard and their "mouse rescue squad" -- is 
in production at Disney. Due out next year, it's the sequel to the "Rescuers" 
(1977). This time, the mice will rescue a little Aboriginal boy from the 
clutches of a mean poacher, assisted by a kangaroo mouse named Jake -- who, we 
are told, is in the Mick Dundee mold. 
