<HEADLINE>
<P>
SINGAPORE ARMY TO STAGE WAR GAMES IN TAIWAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAIPEI, Taiwan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Singapore army will hold a series of military training maneuvers in Taiwan 
this month, a spokesman for Taiwan's Ministry of National Defense said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The war games could involve as many as 10,000 Singaporean troops and will be 
the largest single military exercise staged in Taiwan by the small city-state, 
analysts said. 
</P>
<P>
Singapore has long used Taiwan army facilities to train its troops, but both 
sides have publicly played down their military cooperation until recently. 
</P>
<P>
Singapore has no diplomatic ties with Taipei but unofficial bilateral links are 
strong. 
</P>
