<HEADLINE>
<P>
82-YEAR-OLD MAN CONFESSES TO 8 COLORADO HEISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DENVER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least eight robberies in northern Colorado have been solved by the 
confessions of 82-year-old Jack Kelm, who says he needed the money to 
supplement his Social Security. 
</P>
<P>
Kelm, who was arrested first in 1921 and spent about 40 years in jail, admitted 
the "salt and pepper" heists -- so called because of the assailant's hair color 
-- after he was detained last week for robbing a bank, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Kelm confessed to six robberies of banks, restaurants and supermarkets in Ft. 
Collins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
