<HEADLINE>
<P>
ILLITERATE CANDIDATES BANNED IN IRAQ ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BAGHDAD, Iraq 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iraq has told 42 illiterate parliamentary candidates that they have been 
disbarred from running in Saturday's general elections. 
</P>
<P>
A statement by the ruling Revolutionary Command Council said candidates who did 
not know how to read and write had been dropped from the list of 952 people 
contesting the 250 seats in the National Assembly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
