<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECKLESS SKIING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There is one important issue that was not addressed in "Reckless Skiing Is 
Pursued as a Felony" (Part I, March 23). Being a four-year resident of Mammoth 
Lakes and a four-year resident of Wrightwood (Mt. High) I have seen a lot of 
smoking (marijuana), drinking of alcohol, and on occasion have seen cocaine 
used on chair lifts and gondolas. 
</P>
<P>
Licensing skiers may be a good idea, but skiing under the influence could well 
be the main culprit of skiing accidents and should, therefore, be addressed in 
the studies and discussions regarding skier safety on the slopes. 
</P>
<P>
MONICA MELKONIAN 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
