<HEADLINE>
<P>
OIL SPILL OFF ALASKA SHORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although it is not yet clear how extensively the Valdez oil spill will damage 
the Alaskan coast, the incident serves as a lesson in risk assessment. Certain 
occurrences simply must not be allowed to happen. Therefore, activities that 
could lead to their occurrence, even with very small probability, must not be 
sanctioned. Sometime, somehow, the machines will break down or the humans will 
falter and the dreaded event will take place. 
</P>
<P>
Is all the oil in Alaska worth the destruction of Alaska? Is all the nuclear 
power generated today or in the future worth the destruction that could result 
from an accident or accumulation of radioactive waste? If the answer is no, 
then alternatives, even though they may seem like drastic breaks with our past 
way of thinking, must be developed and instituted. 
</P>
<P>
ROSE CLAUM 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
