<HEADLINE>
<P>
A DIFFERENT VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I'm writing to express my dismay at the change in format and articles written 
in the View section. 
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, there seems a concerted effort to publish pieces geared 
to the sensational and bordering on tabloid journalism. Previously you had 
portraits of achievers who were trying to make a difference -- issue-oriented 
individuals whose selfless lives we admired and whose courage we wanted to 
emulate. Issues of hunger, nuclear war, peace and justice were prominently 
displayed. What happened to the terrific pieces by Kathleen Hendrix and Beverly 
Beyette? 
</P>
<P>
Now there seem to be an excess of the rich and famous -- individuals whose 
contributions are dubious. Who wants to read about Donald Trump or David Duke 
in the wonderful Los Angeles Times? There are plenty of magazines that cater to 
this type of rubbish. Please bring back the old View section. 
</P>
<P>
KAREN FLAHERTY 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
