<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRECIOUS PLANET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alice Kahn should be branded with a scarlet letter "A" for apathetic. In her 
article "Hellbent for Destruction . . . but Have a Nice Day" (March 22), she 
disgusted me with her laissez-faire attitude about environmental concerns. Our 
planet is a wreck, but it is a sorry fact that the majority of people will not 
take action until our environment is practically unbearable, and at the rate we 
are going, that shouldn't take too many more years. 
</P>
<P>
Summing up the evasive point to her article, Kahn finally admits that the 
environmentalists are right, that we need to take action, but she has no clue 
as to what she can do. As concerned inhabitants of this planet, there is plenty 
we can do. For starters, support the environmentalist groups that work for 
hardly any pay at all to keep the planet healthy. 
</P>
<P>
There is Greenpeace, Sane/Freeze, Peta, Save the Bay, and the list goes on. 
Keep informed on current events. Attend lectures, demonstrations, marches and 
rallies. Read. Don't use household products that contain dangerous chemicals. 
</P>
<P>
There are natural alternatives. 
</P>
<P>
Write letters to politicians. Let your voice be heard. Give your attention to 
at least one cause that moves you and you can make a difference. There is no 
time left to just sit there and let others take care of the environment; after 
all, it belongs to all of us. It's everyone's problem. 
</P>
<P>
JENNIFER LAPIERRE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
