<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT WE EAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for Jack Smith's compassionate and self-revealing column, 
"Reflections of Our Animal Appetites." This revelation of consciousness is 
particularly timely in light of the fact that we have discovered that eating 
animal flesh is almost as harmful to the eaters as it is to the eaten 
(although, probably less painful). Since the '50s, because we were wealthy 
enough to pay for it, we Americans have been on an animal food binge and it's 
costing us our lives and our environment. 
</P>
<P>
Old habits die hard. It won't be easy for most of us to give up or cut down on 
animal products, but even the professed carnivore will have to agree that it is 
the only intelligent thing to do. 
</P>
<P>
ARIANE SPADE 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
