<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW EDITOR FOR SECTION NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Merle M. Harpe, deputy suburban editor of The Times for the past two years, 
will become editor of the South Bay edition Monday. 
</P>
<P>
In her new position she will coordinate news and feature coverage for the South 
Bay pages, which are published three times weekly. 
</P>
<P>
Since joining The Times in 1978, Harpe has held a variety of editing positions 
in the paper's Metro, San Diego and Southeast editions. Previously she was an 
editor with the Chicago Daily News. 
</P>
<P>
Harpe replaces Gary M. Gorman, who will become director of The Times' minority 
editorial training program. 
</P>
