<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego Yacht Club will probably appeal a court order to forfeit the 
America's Cup to New Zealand, the president of the America's Cup Organizing 
Committee said. 
</P>
<P>
Malin Burnham, president of the ACOC, said the yacht club board will decide by 
Monday if it wants to proceed with the appeal of New York Supreme Court Justice 
Carmen Ciparick's March 28 ruling awarding the trophy to the Mercury Bay 
Boating Club. 
</P>
<P>
The board of the America's Cup Organizing Committee voted unanimously to 
recommend that the SDYC appeal the court decision. 
</P>
