</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After a protest by Israel, the International Table Tennis Federation placed the 
Pakistan men's team last in its group for missing a match at the World Table 
Tennis Championships at Dortmund, West Germany. 
</P>
<P>
Pakistan was scheduled to play Israel in a second-round match Friday night, but 
did not show up in time, according to organizers of the championship. Pakistan 
forfeited the match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
