<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego's Jess Stayrook won one match in the stepladder final to finish third 
in the $500,000 Seagram's Coolers Open, the richest tournament on the 
Professional Bowlers Assn. tour, at Edmond, Okla. 
</P>
<P>
Stayrook defeated Harry Sullins, 226-195, before losing to eventual champion 
Mike Aulby, 234-222, in the next-to-last match. Stayrook earned $50,000. 
</P>
<P>
Aulby took advantage of three open frames by Jim Pencak for a 195-178 victory 
in the title game. Ge earned $100,000 for his 17th career PBA title and third 
victory this year. He has won three of his last four tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
Aulby has earned $172,985 for the year, a record for the Winter Tour, eclipsing 
Bob Benoit's $155,630 last year. 
</P>
<P>
Aulby grabbed an early lead when Pencak, the top qualifier, missed a single-pin 
spare in the second frame. Pencak fell 22 pins back when he failed to convert a 
split in the third frame. A missed spare by Aulby in the fourth frame got 
Pencak to within five pins, but Aulby then struck on three of his next four 
shots and coasted to the victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
