<HEADLINE>
<P>
BURBANK'S LEWIS WINS 2-MILE RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Todd Lewis of Burbank High clocked 9 minutes, 26.33 seconds to win the 
invitational two-mile run at the Beverly Hills-UCLA Relays at Drake Stadium on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Lewis, the Southern Section 3-A Division cross-country champion, took the lead 
for good after a slowish, 75-second first lap and covered the final 400 meters 
in 63 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
"It was ridiculous," the Bulldog senior said. "It was too slow. I had to take 
it out." 
</P>
<P>
After winning the 800 meters in 1:55.37 at the Pasadena Games last Saturday, 
Lewis ran back-to-back 4:43 miles to outlast Miraleste's Gary Stolz, second in 
9:36.78. 
</P>
<P>
Hart won the 4 x 800 relay (8:09.45) and placed second in the 4 x 1,600 relay 
(18:27.35). Oak Park won the sprint medley (1:33.50) and Birmingham's Sheri-Lee 
Segal (11:53.90) won the girls' invitational two-mile title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
