<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BRIEFS: OFFICE LEASE COSTS DIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thanks to a building-boom generated vacancy factor, office space in Orange 
County is less expensive than it was three years ago. 
</P>
<P>
The county's average monthly lease rate per square foot was $1.65 in the fourth 
quarter of 1988, according to Coldwell Banker. The rate was $1.67 in the fourth 
quarter of 1985 and $1.73 in the fourth quarter of 1987. 
</P>
<P>
The office vacancy factor was 21.7% in the fourth quarter of 1988 -- up from 
15.1% in 1985, according to the commercial realty firm, with 3.6 million square 
feet of space under construction in a market where existing space totals 45.4 
million square feet. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar had the highest average lease rate in Orange County, $2.25 per 
square foot per month, Coldwell Banker reported. Fountain Valley and Yorba 
Linda tied for least expensive, with an average of 95 cents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
