<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
3M BREAKS GROUND ON DISTRIBUTION CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
3M has broken ground on its new West Coast distribution center in Vintage 
Industrial Park in Ontario. The 281,000-square-foot facility at the northwest 
corner of Wineville Avenue and Philadelphia Street is on 42 acres purchased 
from Union Pacific Realty Co. for $9 million. 
</P>
<P>
Architects are Hill-Pinckert of Irvine. Birtcher Construction is general 
contractor for the $6.3-million project. 
</P>
<P>
The distribution center will stock products from 23 3M divisions, including 
office supplies, dental materials and pharmaceuticals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
