<HEADLINE>
<P>
ASSAULT RIFLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This letter is to answer Ann Cox-Clasby of Laguna Beach about her comments on 
state Sen. David A. Roberti's bill on assault rifles (March 19): 
</P>
<P>
Fully automatic firearms have been outlawed by the federal government for at 
least four decades. Guess what: The criminals and drug dealers have them 
anyway. Illegal arms come into this country just like cocaine does: by the ton. 
It has also been against federal law to modify a semiautomatic weapon into a 
fully automatic one. Guess what: The criminals and drug dealers do it anyway. 
</P>
<P>
The laws already exist to deter the criminal, but they are not enforced. 
</P>
<P>
Disarming the law-abiding citizen is unconstitutional, illogical and won't even 
slow down the killing. 
</P>
<P>
LEON M. CANZIANI 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
</TEXT>
